    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="877"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">895.50 Recovery/8–1948</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Director of the Budget</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pace</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lovett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-19">August 19,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lovett</hi>: In accordance with our agreement
                    today, I am enclosing<note n="1" xml:id="d877fn1">Enclosures not attached to
                        file copy. Marginal notations indicated that changes suggested by the
                        Department were accepted by Mr. Pace on August 20.</note> for your comment a
                    proposed memorandum from the President to the effect that economic assistance to
                    Korea shall be undertaken by the Economic Cooperation Administration on January
                    1, 1949 or in no event later than March 15, 1949. Enclosed likewise for your
                    comment is a proposed press statement of the President.</p>
                <p>Because of the top secret nature of the timing for the transfer and the
                    inadvisability of actual transfer at this time, it seems to me on further
                    reflection that a classified Presidential memorandum and a simple public
                    announcement will accomplish all the purposes you have in mind at this time, and
                    that the memorandum can be followed at a later date by the formal Executive
                    order.</p>
                <pb facs="1298" n="1284" xml:id="pg_1284"/>
                <p>I congratulate each of you on the fine spirit of cooperation which made possible
                    our prompt agreement this morning.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank Pace, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
